1:1 COMMENT "# constructors.z -- Constructors, meta.create, and implicit construction"
1:73 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "#"
2:2 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates:"
3:16 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# - Default construction via the compiler-generated `create` (wrapper around"
4:77 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   the internal `meta.create` raw allocator)"
5:46 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "# - Implicit construction: using a type name as a callable routes through"
6:74 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#   the type's `.create` method (see doc/spec.pdoc \"Implicit Construction\")"
7:76 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "# - Explicit `.create` is equivalent to bare-name construction"
8:63 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "# - User-defined `create` with a non-default signature"
9:55 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "# - `meta.create` as the only way to allocate raw fields; called explicitly"
10:76 EOL "\n"
11:1 COMMENT "#   inside the user-defined create body"
11:40 EOL "\n"
12:1 EOL "\n"
